roleplaying

Class AbstractGear

  • java.lang.Object
    • roleplaying.AbstractGear
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Gear>, Gear
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FootGear, HandGear, HeadGear

    public abstract class AbstractGear
extends java.lang.Object
implements Gear
    This abstract class contains all the operations that all types of gears should support. This serves as an encapsulation for the sub gear types and enables ease of code refactoring.

      • compareClass

        public int compareClass(Gear that)
        This method is used in array sorting of objects. Here the object of type gears are compared against each other and are sorted in the following order. Head Gear > Hand Gear > Foot Gear.
        Parameters:

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(Gear gear)
